task.summary: Jumping code, for some reason collision detection code lags the game/breaks gravity and falling
Ok tile collision detection code works, the biggest issue is that there is lag when it collides.
finalized block bound collection(to make player look like hes on the block), the lag issue still remains!
Fixed the lag issue, turns out if you set the for loop to run "int j = i" instead of "int j = 0" it reduces lag.
Fixed Collision Detection issue with first block stuff, now we need to make a way to check the side of the block
Fixed the Lag Issue when you create the level try not to mess with the positioning right now. BTW never Tick the map creation becuase it creates lag.
Added a drawing to see the getBownds to fix it.
Fixed Lag issue, apparently if you update createLevel() the same way we render images it gets rid of lag(the first 5-10 seconds are choppy ,but after that its smooths out)
Collision with Zombie works, lag gone.
Cool little backdrop for menu state, If you can figure out to layer it correctly with game that would be cool.
Cool little backdrop for menu state, If you can figure out to layer it correctly with game that would be cool.
Fixed handler issues. Bullet gets rid of Zombie and itself
Trying to implment auto matic wave spawner and changed the way zombies are killed or removed
